<p>is there a way to validate a wildcard (/*) operator in routing.yml? (symfony 1.2)</p>  <p>Example:</p>  <pre><code>step_1:     url: /:some_param/step_1/*     param: { module: module_name, action: index, step: 1}     requirements:        some_param: "some_regex"        *: "some regex" </code></pre>  <p>Because, like it is now, you can add code after a wildcard param in your url and it will be executet. I want to prevent that.</p>  <p>Example:  <a href="https://www.domain.com/purchase/schritt-1/termine?foo=180000&amp;bar=2015-05-29%22%3E%3Cimg%20src=http://ts.mc0.de/1.gif%20onload=alert%26%2340%3Bdocument.cookie%26%2341%3B%3E" rel="nofollow">https://www.domain.com/purchase/schritt-1/termine?foo=180000&amp;bar=2015-05-29%22%3E%3Cimg%20src=http://ts.mc0.de/1.gif%20onload=alert%26%2340%3Bdocument.cookie%26%2341%3B%3E</a></p>  <p>Thank you!</p>